## Behavoural Contract

Here is the behavioural contract, enforced by our unit tests:

    check_is_stringy()
     [x] returns TRUE for strings
     [x] returns TRUE for integers
     [x] returns TRUE for doubles
     [x] returns TRUE for objects that implement toString
     [x] returns FALSE for objects that do not implement toString
     [x] returns FALSE for NULL
     [x] returns FALSE for arrays
     [x] returns FALSE for TRUE
     [x] returns FALSE for FALSE
     [x] returns FALSE for callable arrays
     [x] returns FALSE for resources

